definitions.definition: A formal objection , especially one by a group .
examples: They lodged a protest with the authorities.

definitions.definition: A collective gesture of disapproval ; a demonstration .
examples: We held a protest in front of City Hall.

definitions.definition: The noting by a notary public of an unpaid or unaccepted bill .
A written declaration , usually by the master of a ship , stating the circumstances attending loss or damage of ship or cargo, etc.
